     "source": [
      "Real time comments: pop up box\n",
      "\n",
      "Why?\n",
      "- Data to user really fast\n",
      "- Increased engagement\n",
      "- Looks awesome\n",
      "- Can sell or trade it\n",
      "\n",
      "http://map.labs.disqus.com\n",
      "\n",
      "See a lot of traffic\n",
      "\n",
      "realertime\n",
      "- active on all sites\n",
      "- tested 'dark' on existing network\n",
      "- 1.5 million concurrent users\n",
      "- 45 thousand incomming\n",
      "- 165 thousand messages/s\n",
      "\n",
      "NOT node.js and mongodb\n",
      "\n",
      "All Python!\n",
      "- Core Django\n",
      "- Start with python first\n",
      "- Also other tech\n",
      "\n",
      "redis, python, nginx, long polling\n",
      "\n",
      "v1:\n",
      "memcache + polling\n",
      "\n",
      "v2:\n",
      "posts -> DISQUS -> redis pub/sub -> Flask <- HA Proxy <- embedded clients\n",
      "\n",
      "v3:\n",
      "posts -> DISQUS -> redis pub/sub -> python gevent server -> redis pub/sub -> Flask <- HA Proxy <- embedded clients\n",
      "\n",
      "v4:\n",
      "posts -> DISQUS -> redis pub/sub -> python gevent server -> http post -> nginx + push stream module <- embedded\n",
      "\n",
      "v5:\n",
      "django -> thoonk queue -> formatter + publishers -> http post -> nginx + push stream module <- embedded\n",
      "\n",
      "\n",
      "Thoonk Queue (on top of redis):\n",
      "- django post_save and post_delete -> queue\n",
      "- Implemented as DFA\n",
      "- provides job semantics (end to end acking, reliable job processing distribution)\n",
      "- Uses zest to store items (ranged queries)\n",
      "\n",
      "Python + gevent:\n",
      "- listen to Thoonk queue\n",
      "- Cleans and formats, compress\n",
      "- publish messages to nginx and firehoses\n",
      "- Publish to all ids (forum, thread, user, post)\n",
      "\n",
      "gevent is nice\n",
      "- Easy to read code\n",
      "- use for IO bound systems\n",
      "\n",
      "http://bitly.com/geventspawn\n",
      "https://gist.github.com/NorthIsUp/3053495\n",
      "\n",
      "Use Data pipelines with Mixins\n",
      "This makes tests composable because each thing has only one step\n",
      "\n",
      "nginx push stream\n",
      "- @wizputer #humblebrag on twitter\n",
      "- handles pub/sub and web server\n",
      "- http://wiki.nginx.org/HttpPushStreamModule\n",
      "\n",
      "measure nginx:\n",
      "- push-stream-status endpoint\n",
      "\n",
      "long(er) polling\n",
      "- Using websockets but moving to EventSource\n",
      "\n",
      "test, measure, repeat\n",
      "\n",
      "dark testing\n",
      "- code in every client\n",
      "- have lots of knobs and switches\n",
      "- Use existing network\n",
      "\n",
      "measure all the things!\n",
      "- esp when numbers don't line up\n",
      "- measuring can be hard distributed\n",
      "- express as -1 and +1 when possible\n",
      "- Sentry for measuring exceptions (django)\n",
      "\n",
      "Pretty graphs\n",
      "\n",
      "lessons\n",
      "- do hard computation early in chain\n",
      "- end-to-end acks are good but expensive\n",
      "- redis/nginx pubsub is effectively free\n",
      "- use greenlets, gevent\n",
      "\n",
      "in-app metrics: Scales"
     ]
